Inspired by Beth at Budget Bytes https://www.budgetbytes.com/2013/03/zesty-tomato-artichoke-pasta/

8-12oz. bow tie pasta
3/4 bag frozen spinach
2 (13 oz.) can artichoke hearts (preferabily whole)
2/3 cup olive oil $0.64
4 clove garlic, minced $0.08
1 tsp dried oregano $0.03
1 tsp dried basil $0.03
1/2 tsp dried thyme $0.02
1/2 tsp dried rosemary $0.02
1/2 tsp red pepper flakes
15-20 cranks freshly cracked pepper
1/2 tsp salt
6 oz. tomato paste
1/2 tsp sugar

Toppings: some grated vegan parmesan or similar (optional)

Boil water with a dash of salt and a splash of olive oil for the bow-tie pasta. 
When water boils, cook 8oz of pasta for about 10 minutes or until aldente. Drain and rinse under cool water.

-In a large pan (3-4 quart) add 2/3 cup olive oil over medium low heat. Mince 4 cloves of garlic
 and add them to the pan.
-Next add to the pan 1 tsp basil, 1 tsp oregano, 1/2 tsp thyme, 1/2 tsp rosemary, 1/2 tsp red pepper flakes, 
 15-20 crankes of black pepper and 1/2 tsp salt. 
-Stir and warm the mixture taking care not to burn the herbs. (about 5 minutes)
-Add the 6oz tomato paste and 1/2 tsp sugar and mix with oil. Heat and stirr for a while, you should notice the bright red of
 the tomato paste take on a darker wine colour.
-Add 1/2 to 3/4 bag frozen spinach to the pan and stir in.
-When the spinach is defrosted, drain 2 cans artichoke hearts and slice the hearts into thin rounds, add to the pan.
-add bow tie pasta into the sauce mixture and toss to coat.

Serve with veg-parm.
